             sworn.</p>
               <p>On Saturday the 20th of March between two and three in the afternoon, I was walking along <placeName id="t17840421-64-crimeloc355">Fleet-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17840421-64-crimeloc355" type="placeName" value="Fleet-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17840421-64-crimeloc355" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17840421-64-off353 t17840421-64-crimeloc355"></join>, one Mr. Stapleton that happened to know me was walking behind me, came and told me I had lost my handkerchief, and I found it was gone, and he pointed to the prisoner, I immediately laid hold of him by the collar, I ripped open his waistcoat immediately, and found the handkerchief between the waistcoat and shirt, I am sure it is my handkerchief, the Constable has it, there was a B upon it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17840421-64-person771">
                  JOHN
                   STAPLETON
               <interp inst="t17840421-64-person771" type="surname" value="STAPLETON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17840421-64-person771" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17840421-64-person771" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>As I was returning from the Temple, I saw the prisoner watching some people, and I saw him turn short round after Mr. Baker, and he put his hand into his pocket, and took his handkerchief out, and put it under his coat, I informed Mr. Baker, and we went across the way after the prisoner, Mr. Baker opened his coat and waistcoat, and found the handkerchief upon him, I am quite sure I saw him take the handkerchief, I saw it found upon him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I have nothing to say.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178403270110"></xptr>
            
